# D365 F&O Debugging Standards

Use when investigating failures in X++ classes or batch logic.

## Before changing code

- Reproduce in **sandbox** — never debug fixes on production
- Capture full **Infolog** message and stack context
- For CoC issues: verify `next` at first level and `[ExtensionOf]` target before editing logic
- For batch failures: read **BatchJobHistory** and job parameters first
- For post-upgrade issues: run **compatibility checker** against baseline

## Avoid

- Shotgun debugging (multiple unrelated changes)
- Fixing symptoms without causal chain (e.g. swallowing exceptions without root cause)
- Using `doUpdate`/`doInsert`/`doDelete` as a "fix" — bypasses CoC and validation

## Invoke

Use `/xpp-fno-debug` or `/xpp-fno-debugger` for systematic investigation. See skill `xpp-fno-debug` and [docs/debugging.md](../docs/debugging.md).
